{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.14",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 14 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:1",
      "text": "Man that is born of a woman is of few days, and full of trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:2",
      "text": "He cometh forth like a flower, and is cut down: he fleeth also as a shadow, and continueth not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:3",
      "text": "And dost thou open thine eyes upon such an one, and bringest me into judgment with thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:4",
      "text": "Who can bring a clean thing out of an unclean? not one.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:5",
      "text": "Seeing his days are determined, the number of his months are with thee, thou hast appointed his bounds that he cannot pass;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:6",
      "text": "Turn from him, that he may rest, till he shall accomplish, as an hireling, his day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:7",
      "text": "For there is hope of a tree, if it be cut down, that it will sprout again, and that the tender branch thereof will not cease.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:8",
      "text": "Though the root thereof wax old in the earth, and the stock thereof die in the ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:9",
      "text": "Yet through the scent of water it will bud, and bring forth boughs like a plant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:10",
      "text": "But man dieth, and wasteth away: yea, man giveth up the ghost, and where is he?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:11",
      "text": "As the waters fail from the sea, and the flood decayeth and drieth up:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:12",
      "text": "So man lieth down, and riseth not: till the heavens be no more, they shall not awake, nor be raised out of their sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:13",
      "text": "O that thou wouldest hide me in the grave, that thou wouldest keep me secret, until thy wrath be past, that thou wouldest appoint me a set time, and remember me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:14",
      "text": "If a man die, shall he live again? all the days of my appointed time will I wait, till my change come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:15",
      "text": "Thou shalt call, and I will answer thee: thou wilt have a desire to the work of thine hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:16",
      "text": "For now thou numberest my steps: dost thou not watch over my sin?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:17",
      "text": "My transgression is sealed up in a bag, and thou sewest up mine iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:18",
      "text": "And surely the mountain falling cometh to nought, and the rock is removed out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:19",
      "text": "The waters wear the stones: thou washest away the things which grow out of the dust of the earth; and thou destroyest the hope of man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:20",
      "text": "Thou prevailest for ever against him, and he passeth: thou changest his countenance, and sendest him away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:21",
      "text": "His sons come to honour, and he knoweth it not; and they are brought low, but he perceiveth it not of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.14.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 14:22",
      "text": "But his flesh upon him shall have pain, and his soul within him shall mourn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
